  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-06-22",
    "date": "2020-10-06T14:33:17Z",
    "text": "We Go Together Act\n\nThis bill requires the President to take certain actions before changing U.S. policy with respect to the U.S.-South Korea Mutual Defense Treaty.\n\nSpecifically, no later than 120 days before making such a change, the President shall provide to Congress (1) a detailed justification for the change, (2) a certification that the change is in the U.S. national interest, and (3) a certification that an alternative agreement or measure is in place to replace any lost capacity or benefits stemming from the change."
